  "description": "Create a new petition, or search and sign other people's petitions to the UK Parliament and government",
  "details": {
    "department_analytics_profile": "",
    "external_related_links": [

    ],
    "introductory_paragraph": "<p>Create or sign a petition that asks for a change to the law or to government policy.</p>\n\n<p>After 10,000 signatures, petitions get a response from the government.</p>\n\n<p>After 100,000 signatures, petitions are considered for debate in Parliament.</p>\n\n<div role=\"note\" aria-label=\"Information\" class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>There’s a different way to <a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://www.parliament.scot/get-involved/petitions/about-petitions\">petition Scottish Parliament</a> and <a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://senedd.wales/senedd-business/petitions/\">petition Welsh Parliament</a>.</p>\n</div>\n",
    "more_information": "<p>You must be a British citizen or a UK resident to create or sign a petition.</p>\n\n<p>You cannot use this service to create a petition:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>about something that Parliament or the government isn’t responsible for</li>\n  <li>about a legal case that’s active in the UK courts</li>\n  <li>that names people working in public bodies (except for senior management)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2 id=\"other-ways-to-petition\">Other ways to petition</h2>\n\n<p>You can also <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.parliament.uk/get-involved/have-your-say/petitions/paper-petitions/\">petition Parliament through your <abbr title=\"Member of Parliament\">MP</abbr></a>.</p>\n\n",
    "start_button_text": "Start now",
    "transaction_start_link": "https://petition.parliament.uk",
    "variants": [

    ],
    "will_continue_on": "the petitions service"
  },
